<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The default branch of the switch is unreachable. The loop iterates for (i = 0; i <= VOLATILE_DISK_LOC_MAX; ++i) and the enum defines enumerators 0..VOLATILE_DISK_LOC_TMP with VOLATILE_DISK_LOC_MAX being the last enumerator value. Every possible i value produced by the loop (0..VOLATILE_DISK_LOC_MAX) is covered by a case label, so control can never reach the default: tmpdir = NULL; statement. This constitutes unreachable code and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1.
</scenario>
